      <hedline>
        <hl1>3 Are Shot in Restaurant</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Three people are shot and wounded in restaurant in East New York section of Brooklyn after argument on sidewalk spills inside (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Three people were shot yesterday in a Brooklyn restaurant after an argument on the sidewalk spilled inside, the police said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Three people were shot yesterday in a Brooklyn restaurant after an argument on the sidewalk spilled inside, the police said.</p>
        <p>Around 4:30 p.m., two young men began arguing in front of the International West Indian Restaurant on New Lots Avenue in East New York, said Officer Gary Cillo, a police spokesman. One of the youths pulled a gun and chased the other youth, 16, into the restaurant, where he began shooting, striking the 16-year-old and two employees, Officer Cillo said. The gunman fled, the officer added.</p>
        <p>The victims were in stable condition last night at Brookdale Hospital.</p>
      </block>
